oai_dc:dc.dc:title: Cabinet card of nine brothers, including John Marshall Dickey
oai_dc:dc.dc:description: This cabinet card shows nine men in dark suits wearing Masonic collars and aprons. From left to right are: John Marshall Dickey, Sr., Gum Dickey, Mart Dickey, Dr. Walter Dickey, Fred Dickey, John Dickey, Frank Dickey, Tom Dickey, and Ace Dickey. John Marshall Dickey, Sr. was a Confederate veteran of the 44th Tenn. Inf. Regt., CSA. The Dickeys lived near Kelso, Lincoln County (Tenn."
